    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-12-14T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-12-14T13:00:00-05:00" n="888"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d888">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">816.51/12–1445: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in El Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gade</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-14T12:00:00-06:00"
                            >December 14, 1945—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 2:39 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>339. In new instructions to Laxton, British Council agrees (1) to change of date
                    to Jan. 1, 1946, (2) to funding bond interest of 3 percent but not 2 percent,
                    and (3) to waiver of customs lien provided (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) lien
                    immediately restored if Salvador borrows fresh money on any specific security
                    whatever and (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) if Salvador borrows without giving
                    security, it will affirm that the three series of the “existing loan rank senior
                    to the new loan”. Before presenting these instructions to Salvadoran Govt,
                    Laxton is thinking of cabling British Council to reconsider. Deptel 205, Dec. 13
                    is being studied.<note n="40" xml:id="d888fn40">Telegram not printed; it quoted
                        a message from the Foreign Bondholders Protective Council to the Embassy
                        (816.51/12–1345).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gade</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
